The lectotype of this species was selected from among several syntypes by Sleumer (1973) . Two sheets of this collection are held at P, one in good condition with multiple flowers and one in poor condition and lacking flowers.Sleumer presumably would have thought primarily of the former as the lectotype, but did not specify this in print and annotated both sheets as “lectotype.” As permitted by Art. 9.17 of the ICN (
McNeill et al. 2012
), we hereby further designate the better-quality duplicate as the lectotype.

